Distribution.
Abditoporella dimorpha
n. sp.
is known from the Gulf of California (
Soule 1961
; Salazar-
Vallejo & Lopez-Muraira 1983
) and Scammon’s Lagoon, Baja California, Mexico (
Soule & Soule 1964
) (as
Hippopodinella adpressa
), and from the coasts of Michoacan and Guerrero, Mexico (present study) (
Figure 2
). Specimens were collected from 0 to 27 m depth, but the species can be found to 73 m (
Soule 1961
).
